Challenge 1: What is the difference between expected value and mean?
\fs40 \cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 You know both concepts but, is there a difference? Are they synonims? \
\
The expected value represents the expected average of the variable that you are investigating, for example :\
the expected value of rolling a 3-sided dice is \cf0 \cb3 (1 * 1/3) + (2 * 1/3) + (3 * 1/3) = 2.\
The mean would be the same (1+2+3)/3= 2.\
However, with the expected value you can give weight to occurrences that are more likely to prevail, since it\'b4s calculated with the probability. The mean is calculated with the actual values that have occurred.\
Both the expected value and the mean are the average of an occurrence.
\f2\fs32 \cf2 \cb3 \
