\f0\b\fs28 \cf2 \cb3 Challenge 2: What is the "problem" in science with p-values?\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0 \cf2 \
The issue is that something can be made significant or non-significant depending on the P-value that is chosen.\
Especially when investigating risks for medicine, this can mean that a risk of the medicine is rejected (because it hasn\'92t been found significant) although that when choosing a different P-value the risk would be accepted.\
Especially for these types of risks, instead of saying something is significant or non-significant, some \'93uncertainty\'94 should be taken into account.
